This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with semantic segmentation, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. The paper also proposes a new method for weakly-supervised semantic segmentation, which involves training a neural network, making it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper involves experiments on a dataset, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper proposes a self-adaptation mechanism, which involves iterative processes, making it likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
